  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6761 sitting above the max negative gamma strike at 6750 (-67.7B), dealers are likely forced to buy this rally as their short gamma position requires them to hedge in the same direction as price movement. The massive negative GEX cluster between 6745-6765 creates a dangerous amplification zone where any sustained move will trigger cascading dealer flows - breaks below 6750 should accelerate selling pressure while moves toward the 6800 positive gamma wall will face increasing dealer resistance. The recent GEX surge event combined with the breakout regime suggests we're in a critical inflection point where momentum in either direction gets amplified rather than dampened.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings with acceleration on any break below 6750 or squeeze toward 6800.",
